    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-10-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-10-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="233"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d233">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 7666/9.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Minister for Foreign Affairs of Mexico</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-10-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 17, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I thank Your Excellency for your telegram 14th instant, inviting the Government
                    of the United States in name Mexican Government to send a delegate to the third
                    international sanitary convention to meet at Mexico City December 2. Invitation
                    so courteously extended will have prompt consideration, and I shall have the
                    honor to answer definitely in a few days.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
